# ── Mobile env example ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy to mobile/.env.local for development. Expo only exposes variables
# prefixed with EXPO_PUBLIC_ to the client bundle at build time.
#
# Production builds (EAS) typically set these via eas.json's per-profile
# `env` block instead — values in mobile/.env.local are picked up by
# `npx expo start` only.

# ── API base (recommended in dev) ────────────────────────────────────────
# Phones can't reach your laptop's "localhost" — find your laptop's LAN IP
# (`ifconfig en0 inet` on macOS, "ipconfig" on Windows) and put it here.
# Without this, mobile falls back to the production API on Render.
#
#   EXPO_PUBLIC_API_BASE=http://192.168.1.42:5000/api

# ── Google OAuth (required for Google login) ─────────────────────────────
# Same client id used by backend/frontend. The hardcoded fallback in
# constants/api.ts works for the bundled production build but should be
# overridden here in dev to keep your environments separate.
#   EXPO_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=xxxx.apps.googleusercontent.com
